{"ts":"2026-06-26T08:13:15.020Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Checking Responsiveness Issues**\n\nI'm currently verifying the responsiveness of the header and footer. Specifically, I'm analyzing the mobile menu's behavior when `isMenuOpen` is true across different viewports. I'm noting the `md:hidden` attribute and its impact on the display of the menu and the header.\n\n\n**Analyzing Navigation Visibility**\n\nI've discovered a significant issue with the navigation's visibility on tablet-sized screens (768px-1023px). Currently, neither the desktop menu nor the mobile trigger is visible due to the conflicting `hidden` attributes: `hidden lg:flex` for desktop and `md:hidden` for mobile. This creates a broken layout where users have no way to navigate. The mobile menu itself is also hidden on these screen sizes. I'm noting this is a great catch and planning a fix to ensure the mobile trigger displays on tablet.\n\n\n"}}
